observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our previous recommendations that:
a. Management require the inventory committee to complete the physical count of the properties and to undertake the said activity annually;
b. The Municipal Treasurer be required to update the ledger cards, property records and Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) in order that the reconciliation of the physical count against book balances can be facilitated;
c. The Municipal Treasurer and OIC – Municipal Accountant reconcile the accounting and property records and make the necessary adjustments so that the accounts can be fairly presented in the financial statements;
d. Update the issuances of AREs and ensure that all movable assets are covered by the same;
e. Require the Property Officer to prepare individual ARE for every property issued and renew the records every three (3) years thereafter pursuant to Section 42 of the NGAS manual, to easily pinpoint responsibility and accountability.
